The paper deals with distributed algorithms for adjusting beamforming vectors and receiver filters in multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) interference networks. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on MIMO interference networks and the use of adaptive algorithms for time-varying channels, it is most likely to belong to the cs.IT sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant, but to a lesser extent.
